body:
I've been playing League of Legends for quite a while now, in fact, since mid-season 2, with few breaks and far between, that also means I've played the game since the "new" queue system was introduced, in which you can select two roles as your preferred roles. Now, lately, I've been focused on Mid and que it up as my main role every game, with Top being the secondary, and I experience getting top A LOT more often than Mid, to give you an idea of what I'm talking about I decided to do a small amount of research. 

In the course of 30 games I got Top roughly 80-90% of the games, I wish I could provide further proof, but you have to simply trust me. Lately this has been worse than ever, and I rarely get my main role, over the last week, me getting Top over Mid has become a meme on our TeamSpeak server. It feels very frustrating and I'm wondering, is anyone else experiencing something similar? Is it possible this could be a bug? It's unbearable. Thanks for help

- Further information - I'm Gold 2, EUW. Main: {{champion:4}}
